{
  "info": {
    "name": "mock.health FHIR API",
    "description": "Synthetic FHIR R4 sandbox with SMART on FHIR 2.0 authorization and US Core 6.1 compliance.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Sign up at [mock.health](https://mock.health)\n2. Set the `api_key` variable to your API key (get one from **Getting Started > Generate API Key**)\n3. Run **FHIR Search & Read > Search Patients** to start exploring\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll requests use `Authorization: Bearer {{api_key}}` by default. SMART on FHIR endpoints use OAuth 2.0 flows.\n\n## Documentation\n\n- [API Docs](https://mock.health/docs)\n- [SMART on FHIR Tutorial](https://mock.health/blog/smart-on-fhir-tutorial)\n- [GitHub](https://github.com/mock-health/samples)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{api_key}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "https://api.mock.health",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "api_key",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "patient_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "app_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "media_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "export_job_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "group_id",
      "value": "all-patients",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "access_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Getting Started",
      "description": "Set up your API key and verify your account. Run these first.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get My Profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/me",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Returns your user profile — user ID, email, account, plan, and API key prefix.\n\nRequires authentication via Auth0 JWT or API key."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate API Key",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (json.api_key) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('api_key', json.api_key);",
                  "        console.log('API key saved to collection variable: ' + json.api_key_prefix + '...');",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/me/api-key",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "me", "api-key"]
            },
            "description": "Generate or rotate your API key. Returns the plaintext key (shown once) and a prefix.\n\n**Important:** The response auto-saves the key to the `api_key` collection variable. All subsequent requests will use it.\n\nIf you already have a key, this revokes it and generates a new one."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "FHIR Search & Read",
      "description": "Read-only FHIR R4 operations. Available on all plans.\n\nThe first request (Search Patients) auto-saves a `patient_id` for use in subsequent requests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Search Patients",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    var bundle = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (bundle.entry && bundle.entry.length > 0) {",
                  "        var patient = bundle.entry[0].resource;",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', patient.id);",
                  "        var name = patient.name[0];",
                  "        console.log('Saved patient_id: ' + patient.id + ' (' + name.given[0] + ' ' + name.family + ')');",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient?_count=10",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "_count", "value": "10" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search for patients. Returns a FHIR Bundle with up to `_count` results.\n\nThe first patient's ID is automatically saved to the `patient_id` variable for use in subsequent requests.\n\n**Common search parameters:**\n- `name` — search by name\n- `birthdate` — e.g. `1970-01-01`\n- `gender` — `male` or `female`\n- `_count` — results per page (default 20, max 200)\n- `_sort` — sort field (e.g. `-_lastUpdated`)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Read Patient",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient/{{patient_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient", "{{patient_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Read a single Patient resource by ID.\n\nRun **Search Patients** first to populate the `patient_id` variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Patient $everything",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient/{{patient_id}}/$everything",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient", "{{patient_id}}", "$everything"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all resources in the patient's compartment — conditions, observations, medications, encounters, procedures, imaging studies, documents, and more.\n\nThis is the fastest way to get a complete picture of a patient."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search Observations",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Observation?patient={{patient_id}}&category=vital-signs&_count=20&_sort=-date",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Observation"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "patient", "value": "{{patient_id}}" },
                { "key": "category", "value": "vital-signs" },
                { "key": "_count", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "_sort", "value": "-date" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search observations for a patient. Defaults to vital signs, sorted newest first.\n\n**Common search parameters:**\n- `category` — `vital-signs`, `laboratory`, `exam`, `survey`, `procedure`\n- `code` — LOINC code (e.g. `8867-4` for heart rate, `9269-2` for GCS)\n- `date` — date range (e.g. `ge2024-01-01`)\n- `_sort` — `-date` for newest first"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search Conditions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Condition?patient={{patient_id}}&_count=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Condition"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "patient", "value": "{{patient_id}}" },
                { "key": "_count", "value": "50" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search conditions (diagnoses) for a patient.\n\n**Search parameters:**\n- `category` — `encounter-diagnosis` or `problem-list-item`\n- `clinical-status` — `active`, `resolved`, `inactive`\n- `code` — SNOMED CT code"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search MedicationRequests",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/MedicationRequest?patient={{patient_id}}&_count=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "MedicationRequest"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "patient", "value": "{{patient_id}}" },
                { "key": "_count", "value": "50" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search medication requests (prescriptions) for a patient.\n\n**Search parameters:**\n- `status` — `active`, `completed`, `stopped`\n- `intent` — `order`, `plan`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search Encounters",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Encounter?patient={{patient_id}}&_count=50&_sort=-date",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Encounter"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "patient", "value": "{{patient_id}}" },
                { "key": "_count", "value": "50" },
                { "key": "_sort", "value": "-date" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search encounters (visits) for a patient.\n\n**Search parameters:**\n- `class` — `AMB` (outpatient), `IMP` (inpatient), `EMER` (emergency)\n- `type` — encounter type SNOMED code\n- `date` — date range"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Search DocumentReferences",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/DocumentReference?patient={{patient_id}}&_count=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "DocumentReference"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "patient", "value": "{{patient_id}}" },
                { "key": "_count", "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search clinical documents (notes, discharge summaries, H&P) for a patient.\n\nDocument content is base64-encoded in `content[0].attachment.data`.\n\n**Search parameters:**\n- `type` — LOINC document type (e.g. `18842-5` for discharge summary)\n- `category` — `clinical-note`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "CapabilityStatement",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/metadata",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "metadata"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the server's CapabilityStatement — supported resource types, search parameters, operations, and SMART security extensions.\n\nThis is a public endpoint (no auth required)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "FHIR Write (Pro Plan)",
      "description": "Create, update, and delete FHIR resources. Requires a Pro plan with a provisioned sandbox.\n\n**Important:** All resources must include the synthetic attestation tag in `meta.tag`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Patient",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/fhir+json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"resourceType\": \"Patient\",\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"tag\": [\n      {\n        \"system\": \"https://mock.health/synthetic-attestation\",\n        \"code\": \"synthetic\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"identifier\": [\n    {\n      \"system\": \"https://mock.health/patient-id\",\n      \"value\": \"test-patient-001\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"name\": [\n    {\n      \"use\": \"official\",\n      \"family\": \"Smith\",\n      \"given\": [\"Jane\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gender\": \"female\",\n  \"birthDate\": \"1990-03-15\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new Patient resource.\n\n**Required:** The `meta.tag` with `synthetic-attestation` is mandatory for all writes. The server rejects resources without it.\n\nReturns the created resource with a server-assigned `id` in the `Location` header."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Patient",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/fhir+json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"resourceType\": \"Patient\",\n  \"id\": \"{{patient_id}}\",\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"tag\": [\n      {\n        \"system\": \"https://mock.health/synthetic-attestation\",\n        \"code\": \"synthetic\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"name\": [\n    {\n      \"use\": \"official\",\n      \"family\": \"Smith\",\n      \"given\": [\"Jane\", \"Marie\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gender\": \"female\",\n  \"birthDate\": \"1990-03-15\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient/{{patient_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient", "{{patient_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Replace a Patient resource. The `id` in the body must match the URL.\n\n**Required:** Synthetic attestation tag in `meta.tag`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Patient",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient/{{patient_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient", "{{patient_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Delete a Patient resource. Returns 204 No Content on success."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Bulk Export",
      "description": "FHIR Bulk Data Access (SMART Backend Services). Export patient data as NDJSON files.\n\nWorkflow: Kick off → Poll status → Download files.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Kick Off Patient Export",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 202) {",
                  "    var contentLocation = pm.response.headers.get('Content-Location');",
                  "    if (contentLocation) {",
                  "        var jobId = contentLocation.split('_jobId=')[1];",
                  "        if (jobId) {",
                  "            pm.collectionVariables.set('export_job_id', jobId);",
                  "            console.log('Saved export_job_id: ' + jobId);",
                  "        }",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" },
              { "key": "Prefer", "value": "respond-async" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Patient/$export?_type=Patient,Condition,Observation",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Patient", "$export"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "_type", "value": "Patient,Condition,Observation" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Start a bulk data export of all patients. Returns 202 Accepted with a `Content-Location` header containing the poll URL.\n\nThe `export_job_id` is auto-saved for the poll and download requests.\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `_type` — comma-separated resource types to include\n- `_since` — only resources updated after this date\n- `_outputFormat` — `application/fhir+ndjson` (default)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Kick Off Group Export",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" },
              { "key": "Prefer", "value": "respond-async" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/Group/{{group_id}}/$export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "Group", "{{group_id}}", "$export"]
            },
            "description": "Start a bulk export scoped to a specific Group. Same workflow as Patient export."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Poll Export Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/$export-poll-status?_jobId={{export_job_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "$export-poll-status"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "_jobId", "value": "{{export_job_id}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Check the status of a bulk export.\n\n- **202** — still processing (check `X-Progress` header)\n- **200** — complete, response body contains download URLs\n- **500** — failed"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Download Export File",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/$export-download/{{export_job_id}}/Patient.ndjson",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "$export-download", "{{export_job_id}}", "Patient.ndjson"]
            },
            "description": "Download an NDJSON file from a completed export. Replace `Patient.ndjson` with the filename from the poll response.\n\nEach line is a complete FHIR resource JSON object."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel Export",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/$export-poll-status?_jobId={{export_job_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", "$export-poll-status"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "_jobId", "value": "{{export_job_id}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cancel a running bulk export job."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Validation",
      "description": "Validate FHIR resources against US Core 6.1.0 profiles.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Validate FHIR Resource",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/fhir+json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/fhir+json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"resourceType\": \"Patient\",\n  \"name\": [\n    {\n      \"family\": \"Smith\",\n      \"given\": [\"Jane\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gender\": \"female\",\n  \"birthDate\": \"1990-03-15\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/validate",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "validate"]
            },
            "description": "Validate a FHIR resource or Bundle against US Core 6.1.0.\n\nReturns an OperationOutcome with:\n- **error** — missing required fields\n- **warning** — missing Must Support fields\n- **information** — conformance confirmation\n\nYou can submit a single resource or an entire Bundle."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Media",
      "description": "Retrieve and render medical images (DICOM, X-ray, CT, MRI).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get DICOM Content",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/media/{{media_id}}/content",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "media", "{{media_id}}", "content"]
            },
            "description": "Download the raw binary content of a Media resource.\n\nFor DICOM images, returns `application/dicom` bytes. For other formats (JPEG, PNG), returns the original bytes.\n\nTo find media IDs, search for ImagingStudy resources and look at the `endpoint` references."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Render as PNG",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/media/{{media_id}}/render",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "media", "{{media_id}}", "render"]
            },
            "description": "Get a browser-displayable PNG preview of a medical image.\n\nConverts DICOM to PNG with proper windowing and rescale. Non-DICOM images are returned as-is."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "SMART on FHIR",
      "description": "SMART App Launch STU2.1 endpoints. These implement the OAuth 2.0 authorization flow for FHIR applications.\n\nSee the [SMART on FHIR tutorial](https://mock.health/blog/smart-on-fhir-tutorial) for a step-by-step walkthrough.",
      "auth": {
        "type": "noauth"
      },
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "SMART Discovery",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/fhir/.well-known/smart-configuration",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["fhir", ".well-known", "smart-configuration"]
            },
            "description": "Step 1 of the SMART launch: discover authorization and token endpoints.\n\nReturns the SMART configuration document with:\n- `authorization_endpoint`\n- `token_endpoint`\n- `scopes_supported`\n- `capabilities`\n\nNo authentication required."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "OpenID Configuration",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/.well-known/openid-configuration",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [".well-known", "openid-configuration"]
            },
            "description": "OpenID Connect discovery document. Required for `sso-openid-connect` capability."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "JWKS",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/smart/jwks",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["smart", "jwks"]
            },
            "description": "JSON Web Key Set for verifying ID tokens issued by the authorization server."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Token Exchange",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "authorization_code" },
                { "key": "code", "value": "{{auth_code}}" },
                { "key": "redirect_uri", "value": "http://localhost:8080/callback" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{app_client_id}}" },
                { "key": "code_verifier", "value": "{{code_verifier}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/smart/token",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["smart", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Exchange an authorization code for an access token (Step 4 of SMART launch).\n\nSupports:\n- `authorization_code` — standard SMART launch\n- `refresh_token` — refresh an expired token\n- `client_credentials` — backend service auth (confidential clients)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "UserInfo",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                { "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}", "type": "string" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/smart/userinfo",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["smart", "userinfo"]
            },
            "description": "OpenID Connect UserInfo endpoint. Returns claims about the authenticated user.\n\nRequires a SMART access token with `openid` scope."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Token Introspect",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
